{
  "texts": [
    "The participants in these studies generally found GeoGebra to be user-friendly and reported that it required only a short period to become proficient in the software.",
    "Doruk et al. (2013) found that the majority of participants considered GeoGebra a valuable tool for teaching mathematics, enabling more effective instruction and overcoming challenges that traditional approaches could not address.",
    "However, some limitations were also identified.",
    "These included difficulties in transcribing mathematical expressions into GeoGebra, errors resulting from the software's over-responsiveness, challenges associated with the use of the latest 3D edition, limitations in teaching basic concepts and a potential decrease in enthusiasm over time, leading to the potential for using the software to become tedious (Doruk et al., 2013).",
    "Erkek and Işıksal-Bostan (2015) encountered issues related to the use of GeoGebra, such as disparities in students' proficiency levels with the system leading to uneven class participation."
  ]
}